The following core rules are included by reference, as defined in
[RFC5234], Appendix B.1: ALPHA (letters), CR (carriage return), CRLF
(CR LF), CTL (controls), DIGIT (decimal 0-9), DQUOTE (double quote),
HEXDIG (hexadecimal 0-9/A-F/a-f), HTAB (horizontal tab), LF (line
feed), OCTET (any 8-bit sequence of data), SP (space), and VCHAR (any
visible [USASCII] character).

As a convention, ABNF rule names prefixed with "obs-" denote
"obsolete" grammar rules that appear for historical reasons.

>>>> 1) Receive la requete correctement en fonction des headers
>>>> 2) Check si la requete est correcte au niveau du parsing (peut se faire au fur et à mesure)
>>>> 3) Pour GET: voir si la requete est authorizee, puis content negociation
>>>> 4) Ajout des Headers
>>>> 5) envoi

